6. Difference between HashSet and TreeSet
• HashSet: Uses a hash table; it offers constant-time performance but provides no guarantee of order. 
• TreeSet: Uses a Tree structure; it is slower than HashSet but maintains elements in a sorted/natural order. 

7. Difference between Array and ArrayList 
• Array: Has a fixed size once created and can hold both primitives and objects. 
• ArrayList: A dynamic-sized collection that can grow or shrink automatically; it can only hold objects (uses "wrappers" for primitives). 

